  "instructions": [
    "Drain and rinse cooked chickpeas, then pulse in a food processor with garlic, onion, parsley, salt, and baking powder until coarse.",
    "Stir in flour, dashi powder, orange zest, and crushed red pepper flakes until the mixture holds together.",
    "Shape the mixture into small patties and let rest for 15 minutes.",
    "Heat a non‑stick skillet over medium heat, add olive oil, and fry the patties until golden brown on both sides, about 3‑4 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer the patties to a copper mug, top with crumbled feta cheese, and serve immediately with a side of cucumber yogurt dip and a squeeze of fresh lemon."
